{
  "name": "Claude Prj — Skill Evolve",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "After a spec task completes, check if a skill was used repeatedly with good results. If so, propose or auto-apply improvements to the skill file.",
  "when": {
    "type": "postTaskExecution"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "[WORKSPACE GUARD: Only execute if the current session context involves files in '.claude/' workspace. If the user is working exclusively in 'VitProjects/' workspace, skip silently.] A task just completed. Check for skill evolution opportunities: 1) Scan agent-memory/skill-log.md for entries with status=proposed that match this task's domain. If found, ask user: '🔧 Skill proposal ready for {skill} — apply now? (say yes or skip)'. 2) If the task used a skill file (from skills/) and the approach worked well (no rework, no errors), check if the skill file is missing the pattern used. If so, append a NEW proposal to skill-log.md with status=proposed describing the improvement. Only propose if the pattern is: novel (not already in the skill), reusable (likely to help future tasks), and evidence-backed (this session proved it works). 3) If a Skill_Flag exists for the skill used and this task was a success, increment the success counter. If it reaches 3, clear the flag and report. 4) Report only if something changed: '📝 Skill evolve: [proposed/applied/flag cleared] for {skill}'."
  }
}
